oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Franklin Female Institute
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Student body of the Franklin Female Institute, posed outside the front porch of the building.

The Tennessee Female College was organized in 1857 as a place of higher learning for young women. After the first building burned in 1886, a three-story brick structure with tower served Franklin until it was demolished in 1916.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
